"content": "<p>Various objects were given an outer coating to fit them for their particular purpose.</p>\n<h2>An outer coating given to various objects</h2>\n<h3>An outer coat of pitch made wood and papyrus waterproof</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:14\">GEN 6:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:3\">EXO 2:3</a></p>\n<h3>An outer coat of plaster made stone suitable for writing on</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:2-Deut27:4\">DEU 27:2–27:4</a></strong></p>\n<h3>An outer coat of glaze rendered earthenware suitable for food use</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:23\">PRO 26:23</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Coats of armour for protection</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:14\">2CH 26:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:4-1Sam17:7\">1SA 17:4–17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:38\">1SA 17:38</a></p>\n<h2>Coat used metaphorically</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:13-Job41:17\">JOB 41:13–41:17</a></strong></p>",
